## 1. The R-Ratio
The **R-Ratio** is the fundamental metric of the R-Model, defining the balance between system decay and expansion.

* **Definition:** The ratio of even steps (decay) to odd steps (expansion) across trajectories.
* **Formula:** $R = \text{total\_even\_steps} / \text{total\_odd\_steps}$
* **Critical Threshold:** $\log_2(3) \approx 1.585$
    * This is the minimum ratio required for the decay gate to overcome expansion ($2^R = 3$).

